The following steps are written using Android Studio version 3.5.2.
The app's minimum SDK version is Android 8.0 Oreo (API 26).

Build and run:
  1. Download this project and open it in Android Studio.
  
  2. In the toolbar, select app from the run configurations drop-down menu (center part of the upper toolbar).
  
  3. From the target device drop-down menu (next to configuration drop-down menu), 
  select the device that you want to run the app on.
  If you don't have any devices configured, then you need to either connect a device
  via USB or create an AVD (Android Virtual Device) to use the Android Emulator
  
  More info on connecting a device via USB: https://developer.android.com/studio/run/device#connect
  More info on creating an AVD: https://developer.android.com/studio/run/managing-avds#createavd
  
  4. Click Run (green play button)
